{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Lightly grease Varoma dish and tray and set aside. Place kaffir lime leaves in mixing bowl and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add green beans and spring onions and chop <b>6-8 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add white fish fillets, Thai red curry paste, coconut cream, egg white and salt and chop <b>Turbo\/1 sec\/3 times<b>, or until mix is well combined but not puréed.","Roll mixture into 18 equal-sized balls (approx. 1 heaped Tbsp each) and gently flatten each ball to form fish cakes. Place several fish cakes in prepared Varoma dish and tray, being careful not to let fish cakes touch.","Place water in mixing bowl and place Varoma into position. Steam <b>16 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Transfer to a plate and keep warm.","Place remaining fish cakes in Varoma dish and tray, place Varoma into position and steam <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Serve fish cakes warm, garnished with chilli."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["oil, for greasing","2 - 4 fresh kaffir lime leaves (see tip), stalks removed","100 g fresh green beans, trimmed","2 spring onions (approx. 40 g), cut in pieces","600 g white fish fillets (e.g. cod, haddock), cut in pieces (3-4 cm)","30 - 50 g Thai red curry paste, to taste","60 g coconut cream","1 egg white","½ - 1 tsp salt, to taste","1000 g water","1 long red chilli, thinly sliced, to garnish"]}],"id":"r151908","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-yJWob77sZrU\/XZQwth5jBmI\/AAAAAAAAcoA\/KPRslgQ72sU1qUQTsqYJHXBIEJEqlKcRACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_debZib8RFs_CtUzv.png","title":"Steamed Thai-style fish cakes","publishedAt":"2018-04-10T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"22 g","fat":"11 g","uom":"per 3 pieces","carbohydrates":"4 g","calories":"840 kJ \/ 202 kcal"},"basicInfo":["easy","15m","45m","18 pieces"]}